## üî¨ Minimal Reproduction
just generate an new angular 11 workspace with one library (named 'lib') and change the generated component to:
```ts
@Component({
  selector: 'lib-lib',
  template: `
    <p [outerHTML]="html">
      lib works!
    </p>
  `
})
export class LibComponent {
  @Input() html: string;
}
```
change the generated test case to:
```ts
  it('should create', () => {
    expect(component).toBeTruthy();
    let content = (<HTMLElement>fixture.nativeElement).textContent;
    expect(content).not.toContain('test', 'not set yet');

    component.html = 'test';
    fixture.detectChanges(); // break somewhere in here
    content = (<HTMLElement>fixture.nativeElement).textContent;
    expect(content).toContain('test', 'html var should take over template');
  });
```
running `ng test` will fail as indicated before second assertion


